---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Learning | Amid the Noise">
  <section class="section" data-pagefind-ignore>
    <article>
      <h1>Learning</h1>
      <p class="learning-operator">
        I study how people and systems learn, adapt, and make sense of complex environments.
      </p>
      <p class="learning-intro">
        Selected field work and research across design, civic systems, and human-computer interaction.
      </p>

      <div class="learning-grid" aria-label="Learning section overview">
        <a class="learning-card" href="#field-work">
          <span>Field Work</span>
          <p>Hands-on experience in product and civic systems.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="learning-card" href="#research">
          <span>Research</span>
          <p>Exploration of systems thinking and decision-making.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="learning-card" href="#writing">
          <span>Writing</span>
          <p>Essays and analysis on complexity and design.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section learning-list" data-pagefind-ignore>
    <h2 id="field-work">Field Work</h2>

    <article class="learning-entry">
      <h3>Evernote</h3>
      <p>For the Skitch product, we observed preschool children fingerpaint to understand how people explore color before constraint. The work shifted markup palettes from rigid selection toward more fluid exploration.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="learning-entry">
      <h3>Yahoo!</h3>
      <p>Through improvisation training at Stanford, we practiced building on each other’s ideas while working on Yahoo! frontdoor experiences at global scale. Nearly a billion unique users visited each month, so even fractional A/B tests reached millions.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="learning-entry">
      <h3>Civic Systems</h3>
      <p>Work inside election operations showed how civic systems behave when procedures meet real edge cases. The lesson was simple: interpretation determines whether participation and trust hold under pressure.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .learning-operator {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .learning-intro {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .learning-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 34px;
    max-width: 56rem;
  }

  .learning-card {
    display: block;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: 18px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .learning-card:hover,
  .learning-card:focus-visible {
    border-color: var(--text);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .learning-card span {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .learning-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .learning-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .learning-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .learning-entry {
    padding: 1.1rem 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .learning-entry h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .learning-entry p {
    margin: 0.3rem 0;
  }

  .learning-list h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color, #e5e7eb);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .learning-list h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }
</style>